</section>

<section id="examtips">
<p class="popuptext">You will see from the headings in the table and the information given that you will hear someone talking about the different methods of study. You will hear the lecturer talk about who is invited, what they do and the purpose behind the method. You will also see that you have to complete the table horizontally, row by row.</p>
<p class="popuptext1"><b>Question 1</b></p>
<p class="popuptext2">What part of speech follows 'draw attention to'? You should be listening out for a noun or noun phrase. What do you think is brought to the students' attention in a lecture?</p>
<p class="popuptext1"><b>Question 2</b></p>
<p class="popuptext2">The word 'between' should indicate to you that two numbers will follow.</p>
<p class="popuptext1"><b>Question 3</b></p>
<p class="popuptext2">You should see that you have the subject here so need a verb as the next word. What do you think the tutor and students do in a seminar?</p>
<p class="popuptext1"><b>Question 4</b></p>
<p class="popuptext2">What should follow 'help to'?</p>
<p class="popuptext1"><b>Question 5</b></p>
<p class="popuptext2">What do you think students need help with?</p>
<p class="popuptext1"><b>Question 6</b></p>
<p class="popuptext2">Read the rest of the row in the table. What is the name of a method of study whereby you get practical experience?</p>
<p class="popuptext1"><b>Question 7</b></p>
<p class="popuptext2">What else do students do after they have done some research?</p>
<p class="popuptext1"><b>Question 8</b></p>
<p class="popuptext2">Read the rest of the row. What kind of skills do you think students might be developing?</p>
</section>
